With some vector data-sets (points, lines and areas) it is possible to generate a link (URL) direct to an object on the map. 
When “Object information” is viewed, the bottom line is “Link to object”. One click centres the object in the current window; 
a double click opens it in a new window with the object centred. The “Link” function can then be used to copy the URL then save it or send it in an e-mail.
